<div class="imageleft">
<img src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/CarverJohnson-b.jpg" alt width height border="1" />
<br/>
<div class="phototagleft">
</div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:16px"><strong>Quinn Carver Johnson </strong>(they/them) is the author of <em><a href="https://nupress.northwestern.edu/9780810146501/the-perfect-bastard/">The Perfect Bastard</a></em> (Curbstone Books, 2023), a poetry collection about gender, sexuality, class, and pro wrestling. Their work has appeared in <em>Rappahannock Review</em>, <em>Right Hand Pointing</em>, <em>Cimarron Review</em>, <em>Red Earth Review</em>, and elsewhere. Carver Johnson graduated from Hendrix College and currently lives in Tulsa, where they host the People’s Poetry reading series dedicated to protest poetics.</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
